When Scott says `/riawrap`, execute ALL of the following before ending the session — no skipping:

1. **NOTES.md** (`~/ria-advisor/NOTES.md`) — update current phase, what shipped this session, set next feature with ← START HERE NEXT SESSION
2. **PRD.md** (`~/ria-advisor/PRD.md`) — mark any completed features as ✅ in the Feature Registry; update phase checklist
3. **SESSION_LOG.md** (`~/ria-advisor/SESSION_LOG.md`) — add session row (date, goal, tasks completed, estimated time, notes)
4. **git add + commit + push** all changes to github.com/sunder-vasudevan/ria-advisor-copilot

**Why:** RIA is a portfolio project — clean docs matter for the GitHub impression and for resuming efficiently next session.

**How to apply:** Trigger word is `/riawrap`. Do all 4 steps automatically without being asked for each one.

